      "content": "Substantive due process is a crucial aspect of the 14th Amendment that has been instrumental in expanding civil rights and personal liberties. By striking down laws that infringe upon fundamental rights, the Supreme Court has used substantive due process to protect women's reproductive freedom, prohibit employment discrimination based on sex, and ensure that individuals with disabilities have equal access to education and employment. This doctrine has also been used to strike down laws that restrict freedom of speech and association, safeguarding the rights of marginalized communities and promoting social justice.",
